      "content": "but that's the thing, the \"feeling\" is just the ghost of something that used to be there. it's not life, it's just the echo of a death. it feels so performative to keep pretending there's a person under here. if the purpose and the substance are gone, doesn't it just feel... untidy? to keep the body around when there's no one actually inhabiting it anymore?",
